Antoine continuously strives to enhance his knowledge and expertise in this area, using it as a cornerstone for his professional development. His enthusiasm is clearly reflected in the numerous pyATS articles he has authored for Cisco blogs, showcasing his expertise and offering valuable insights to the tech community.

His articles are not just a testament to his deep understanding of the subject matter, but also a reflection of his ability to communicate complex concepts in an engaging and understandable way. Antoine's unique blend of technical acumen, writing prowess, and practical experience in Solutions Engineering sets him apart in his field. His body of work and continuous learning attitude makes him a valued figure in the tech community.

items.abstract:
For Customers, thorough validation of new release and product is crucial before they are moved into production. However, relying solely on manual testing can be time-consuming, leading to delays and potential risks. What if you could accelerate this process and gain peace of mind by leveraging automation? Join us in this immersive session as we delve into the world of NetOps automation, focusing on building a reusable feature validation test suite using Cisco pyATS.

We will guide you through the journey, starting with the foundational elements such as pyATS core libraries and parsers. As we progress, we will explore the advanced capabilities of the AETest testing framework and how it can be combined with pyATS Easypy module. Finally, we will culminate the session with a compelling customer-based example of SR-TE feature validation using each building block.

This real-world scenario will demonstrate how pyATS empowers network engineers to automate and streamline the validation of IOS XR features. At the end of this lab, participants should be able to use pyATS for feature validation and extend it to their own use cases/environments. Embracing NetOps automation with Cisco pyATS, can not only accelerate the testing process but also achieve enhanced reliability, shortened time-to-production, and increased confidence in the quality of your network deployments.

Attendee is expected to have intermediate Python knowledge (condition, loop, class, object concepts) and be familiar with basic IOS XR CLI. pyATS will be covered from scratch. Attendee is not expected to have any prior experience with pyATS.
